    "Thus, each lookup table may consume 3 to 8 inputs, depending on a different FPGA architecture.",
    "Whereas generally, memory is measured in KB [26].",
    "The program or algorithm must be stored in ROM, whereas intermediate values must be kept in RAM.",
    "• Clock Cycles: The speed of a PC processor, or CPU, is dictated by the clock cycle, which measures the time between two beats of an oscillator.",
    "As a rule, the higher the number of pulses every second, the quicker the PC processor will almost certainly process data."
